  "text": "is the square of the stretch of the fiber; m 0 the fiber direction in the reference configuration; C 3 scales the exponential stress and C 4 is related to the rate of collagen uncrimping. The strain rate effect is visible in the stress-strain curves obtained by [CITATION_1] for the human ACL (Fig. 5) . In order to fit the material parameters and compare the strain rate curves obtained, we reproduced the tensile test in [CITATION_2] Using the proposed anisotropic visco-hyperelastic model, the stress-strain curves obtained at different strain rates (0.012% s À1 , 25% s À1 , 38% s À1 and 50% s À1 ) were well fit, see Fig. 5a . On the contrary, when an isotropic visco-hyperelastic model was used, the stress-strain curve under low strain rate was not well fit. This is due to the significance of the viscoelastic properties of the matrix under low strain rates being not possible to simulate the behaviour of the ligament using the same properties of the matrix and fibers. The elastic and viscoelastic parameters obtained in both cases are included in Table 4 .",
